article.headline: Douglas drops 16 points, including clutch free throws
article.linkText: Douglas rises to occasion as Sun edge Mystics
article.story:
WASHINGTON (AP) -- Katie Douglas scored 16 points, including four
free throws in the final 38 seconds, to lead the Connecticut Sun to
a 69-67 victory over the Washington Mystics on Sunday.

Nykesha Sales scored 13 points and Taj McWilliams-Franklin added
10 points and six rebounds for the Sun.

Chasity Melvin led the Mystics with 15 points and seven rebounds
in their home opener. Temeka Johnson added 12 points and DeLisha
Milton-Jones scored 10 for Washington.

McWilliams-Franklin gave Connecticut a 63-61 lead with two free
throws with 2:16 remaining. Sales extended the lead to 65-61 on a
jumper with 58 seconds left.

"That shot pretty much broke our back because we really had the
momentum," said Milton-Jones, acquired from Los Angeles in the
offseason for Chamique Holdsclaw. "That shot really put a dagger
in our hearts."

After Douglas made two free throws, Laurie Koehn's 3-pointer
pulled the Mystics to 67-64 with 11 seconds remaining. Douglas was
fouled again and made two free throws with 5.3 seconds left for a
69-65 lead before Koehn hit another 3-pointer at the buzzer.

Koehn finished with 12 points on four 3-pointers.

"The effort was there, but our precision isn't here yet,"
Mystics coach Richie Adubato said.

Margo Dydek, who had four blocks, gave Connecticut its first
lead at 30-29 on a three-point play with 2:56 remaining in the
first half. Douglas and Lindsay Whalen converted three-point plays
in the final minute that gave the Sun a 40-35 halftime lead.

Mystics guard Alana Beard missed the game with a right ankle
sprain. Her status is day to day.
